COPY public.disciplines (id, slug, title, subtitle, display_count, hue, body, chapter_title_a, chapter_title_b, tagline, lede, overview, hero_image_id, seo_title, seo_description, seo_og_image_id, seo_canonical, seo_noindex, sort_order, updated_at, created_at) FROM stdin;
2	reconstructive	Reconstructive Surgery	Breast · Trauma · Craniofacial	3 specialties	5	{"root": {"type": "root", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "Reconstructive plastic surgery after cancer, trauma, or congenital conditions — led by craniomaxillofacial-credentialed surgeons in our ACHSI-accredited theatres.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": "ltr", "textFormat": 0}], "direction": "ltr"}}	Reconstructive	surgery.	Chapter II.02 — Reconstructive Surgery	Reconstruction after cancer, trauma, or congenital conditions — performed by ISAPS- and craniomaxillofacial-credentialed surgeons in our ACHSI-accredited theatres, often in coordination with oncology teams in your home country.	{"root": {"type": "root", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "Reconstructive plastic surgery sits at the technical and emotional centre of our practice. Many of our reconstructive patients are travelling for work that is unavailable, expensive, or rushed in their home country — breast reconstruction after cancer, scar revision after trauma, cleft repair where local expertise is limited. We work slowly, coordinate carefully with home-country teams, and provide full surgical documentation for insurance.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": "ltr", "textFormat": 0}], "direction": "ltr"}}	52	\N	\N	\N	\N	f	1	2026-05-25 02:06:52.624+00	2026-05-20 12:44:00.83+00
3	non-surgical	Non-surgical	Injectables · Laser · Skin	12 protocols	1	{"root": {"type": "root", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "Quiet, expert hands for the everyday refinements — neuromodulators, dermal fillers, laser resurfacing and medical-grade facials.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": "ltr", "textFormat": 0}], "direction": "ltr"}}	Quiet hands,	everyday work.	Chapter II.02 — Non-surgical	Injectables, lasers, and skin medicine practiced with the same care as our surgical work — for the small, considered refinements between bigger decisions.	{"root": {"type": "root", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "Non-surgical aesthetics is, at its best, almost invisible work. Our protocols are conservative; our injectors are slow; our laser settings are dialled to the minimum effective dose. The result is the one no one notices — only that you look rested.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": "ltr", "textFormat": 0}], "direction": "ltr"}}	53	\N	\N	\N	\N	f	2	2026-05-25 02:08:02.848+00	2026-05-20 12:44:00.852+00
4	hair	Hair Restoration	FUE & Follicle Therapy	3 protocols	2	{"root": {"type": "root", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "Follicular unit extraction and PRP-based therapies, performed over considered single-day or staged sessions.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": "ltr", "textFormat": 0}], "direction": "ltr"}}	Returning,	quietly.	Chapter II.03 — Hair Restoration	Follicular unit extraction and PRP-based therapies, performed over considered single-day or staged sessions — to restore hairlines without ever announcing them.	{"root": {"type": "root", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "Hair restoration, done well, is impossible to detect. We work with sapphire FUE and DHI techniques, place follicles one at a time, and design hairlines that respect what your face has always done. A single graft, placed badly, is more visible than a thousand placed well.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": "ltr", "textFormat": 0}], "direction": "ltr"}}	55	\N	\N	\N	\N	f	3	2026-05-25 02:09:44.606+00	2026-05-20 12:44:00.877+00
1	surgical	Plastic Surgery	Rhinoplasty · Breast · Body	9 procedures	0	{"root": {"type": "root", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "Considered surgical work performed in our ACHSI-accredited theatres — from rhinoplasty and rejuvenation to breast and body contouring.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": "ltr", "textFormat": 0}], "direction": "ltr"}}	The art of	refinement.	Chapter II.01 — Surgical	Considered surgical work performed in our ACHSI-accredited theatres — from rhinoplasty and facial rejuvenation to breast and body contouring.	{"root": {"type": "root", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "Surgery, in our view, is a quiet conversation. We begin not with what we can do but with what your face and body already do well — and we make our recommendations from there. Our plastic surgeons hold ISAPS and FICS credentials, with fellowship training in Korea, Japan, and Singapore; they perform between three and four cases a day, never more, in theatres that meet international accreditation standards.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": "ltr", "textFormat": 0}], "direction": "ltr"}}	51	\N	\N	\N	\N	f	0	2026-05-25 03:27:18.672+00	2026-05-20 12:44:00.803+00
5	dental	Dental Aesthetics	Veneers · Alignment · Whitening	5 services	3	{"root": {"type": "root", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "The smile, refined. Porcelain veneers, clear alignment, professional whitening — paced to suit your visit.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": "ltr", "textFormat": 0}], "direction": "ltr"}}	The smile,	refined.	Chapter II.04 — Dental Aesthetics	Porcelain veneers, clear alignment, and considered whitening — paced to suit your visit, performed in a small dental studio attached to the clinic.	{"root": {"type": "root", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "We approach a smile the way we approach a face: as something that should look like the person, only at their best. Our dental studio is small — two surgeries, one ceramicist on staff — and we sequence treatment over your visit so that the final smile is delivered in calm, considered stages.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": "ltr", "textFormat": 0}], "direction": "ltr"}}	56	\N	\N	\N	\N	f	4	2026-05-25 02:10:30.375+00	2026-05-20 12:44:00.905+00
6	recovery	Weight Loss	Medical · Endoscopic · Bariatric	3 pathways	4	{"root": {"type": "root", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "Medical weight-loss programmes, endoscopic procedures, and bariatric surgery — paced to suit your goals, with structured nutritional and behavioural support.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": "ltr", "textFormat": 0}], "direction": "ltr"}}	Weight loss,	considered.	Chapter II.06 — Weight Loss	Medical, endoscopic, and bariatric pathways — paced by your goals and supported by nutrition, behavioural, and metabolic specialists from first consult through twelve months of follow-up.	{"root": {"type": "root", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "Weight loss is one of the most multidisciplinary parts of our practice — and one where we move slowest. We require a structured pre-programme for any surgical or endoscopic pathway: nutrition, psychology, behavioural coaching. Patients who arrive expecting a fast intervention are typically directed first to medical pathways; surgical and endoscopic options follow only when supported by twelve weeks of preparation.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": "ltr", "textFormat": 0}], "direction": "ltr"}}	57	\N	\N	\N	\N	f	5	2026-05-25 02:11:24.518+00	2026-05-20 12:44:00.933+00
\.
COPY public.sub_categories (id, slug, parent_id, title, chapter_title_a, chapter_title_b, tagline, lede, intro, overview, lead_surgeon_id, hero_image_id, seo_title, seo_description, seo_og_image_id, seo_canonical, seo_noindex, sort_order, updated_at, created_at) FROM stdin;
2	surgical-body	1	Body	Body,	in proportion.	Contouring with the same restraint as our facial work.	Liposculpture, abdominoplasty, and post-pregnancy or post-weight-loss restoration — performed under our highest safety thresholds, with surgeon-supervised recovery.	\N	{"root": {"type": "root", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "Body work is rewarding when it suits your anatomy and your life — and ill-advised when it doesn't. We will quote you for what we believe is safe and sensible, sometimes less than you came in expecting. Our consultations include a frank conversation about non-surgical alternatives where they might serve you better.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": "ltr", "textFormat": 0}], "direction": "ltr"}}	1	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	f	1	2026-05-20 12:55:41.863+00	2026-05-20 12:54:44.43+00
4	reconstructive-breast	2	Breast Reconstruction	Breast	reconstruction.	Restoration after mastectomy, with proportion and symmetry in mind.	Implant-based and autologous (DIEP, TRAM) breast reconstruction after mastectomy — performed by ISAPS-credentialed reconstructive surgeons, often in coordination with oncology teams in your home country.	\N	{"root": {"type": "root", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "Our reconstructive practice is a small subset of our overall surgical volume — by design. We perform DIEP, TRAM, and implant-based reconstructions; we coordinate with international oncologists via your concierge; and we provide full surgical documentation for insurance claims, which often cover reconstruction in part or whole.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": "ltr", "textFormat": 0}], "direction": "ltr"}}	4	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	f	3	2026-05-20 12:55:41.999+00	2026-05-20 12:54:44.59+00
5	reconstructive-trauma	2	Trauma & Scar	Trauma &	scar repair.	Reconstruction after injury, burn, or unsatisfactory prior surgery.	Scar revision, burn reconstruction, skin grafts, and complex flap repair — for patients seeking refinement after trauma, surgery, or burn injury.	\N	{"root": {"type": "root", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "Our reconstructive team includes a fellowship-trained burn and trauma reconstructive surgeon. We offer everything from minor scar revision under local anaesthetic to complex multi-stage flap reconstruction. We will not promise scar erasure — no surgeon honestly can — but we can almost always improve.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": "ltr", "textFormat": 0}], "direction": "ltr"}}	3	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	f	4	2026-05-20 12:55:42.055+00	2026-05-20 12:54:44.663+00
6	reconstructive-craniofacial	2	Craniofacial	Craniofacial &	reconstructive.	Complex facial reconstruction by craniomaxillofacial subspecialists.	Cleft lip and palate, maxillofacial trauma, orbital reconstruction, and microtia ear reconstruction — performed by our craniomaxillofacial-credentialed surgeon with international fellowship training.	\N	{"root": {"type": "root", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "We treat congenital craniofacial conditions, post-traumatic deformities, and complex acquired conditions of the face, skull, and jaw. Many of our craniofacial patients are referred through international charity and aid networks; we maintain a small pro-bono pathway alongside our private practice.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": "ltr", "textFormat": 0}], "direction": "ltr"}}	4	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	f	5	2026-05-20 12:55:42.134+00	2026-05-20 12:54:44.709+00
7	non-surgical-injectables	3	Injectables	Quiet hands,	small refinements.	Less product, less heat, less everything you might expect.	Botulinum toxin, dermal fillers, bio-remodelling and skin-quality injectables — performed by medical injectors, never technicians, with a deliberately conservative protocol.	\N	{"root": {"type": "root", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "We work to a single principle: that the best injectable work is the kind that nobody sees. Health Canada and TGA-approved products only; medical injectors only; private treatment rooms only. We never run promotional pricing on injectables, because it changes the conversation in a way we are not comfortable with.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": "ltr", "textFormat": 0}], "direction": "ltr"}}	5	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	f	6	2026-05-20 12:55:42.198+00	2026-05-20 12:54:44.764+00
9	non-surgical-skin	3	Skin Health	Skin,	considered.	Medical facials and structured skin protocols.	Medical-grade facials, peels, and structured at-home skin protocols — designed for skin that needs more than maintenance but less than intervention.	\N	{"root": {"type": "root", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "Our medical facials use cosmeceutical-grade product (SkinCeuticals, ZO Skin Health, Obagi) and are delivered by trained skin therapists working alongside the medical team. Every protocol begins with skin diagnosis, ends with a take-home plan, and includes review at six weeks.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": "ltr", "textFormat": 0}], "direction": "ltr"}}	5	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	f	8	2026-05-20 12:55:42.338+00	2026-05-20 12:54:44.877+00
11	hair-therapy	4	Follicle Therapy	Strengthening,	before surgery.	Therapy first; surgery only when therapy can't.	PRP, polynucleotides, and topical protocols — for patients with active follicles that are weakening, where transplant would be premature.	\N	{"root": {"type": "root", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "Therapy is best suited to patients whose follicles are still active but weakening. We assess miniaturisation, donor density, and your timeline; then design a programme that gives therapy a fair trial before considering surgery.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": "ltr", "textFormat": 0}], "direction": "ltr"}}	1	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	f	10	2026-05-20 12:55:42.521+00	2026-05-20 12:54:44.972+00
13	dental-alignment	5	Alignment	Aligned,	quietly.	Clear aligners and lingual alternatives, planned around your travel.	Clear alignment and discrete orthodontic options for adults — scanned, planned, and started during a single Bali visit, then maintained remotely.	\N	{"root": {"type": "root", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "We use Invisalign, ClearCorrect, and a Korean-Japanese lingual system for cases where aligners aren't suitable. Treatment ranges from six to eighteen months depending on complexity. Remote reviews quarterly; in-person review when convenient.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": "ltr", "textFormat": 0}], "direction": "ltr"}}	2	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	f	12	2026-05-20 12:55:42.653+00	2026-05-20 12:54:45.126+00
14	dental-whitening	5	Whitening	Brighter,	without overdoing it.	Professional whitening protocols — for natural-looking results, not Hollywood ones.	In-chair professional whitening, take-home protocols, and combined approaches — calibrated for natural-looking brightness rather than aggressive shade changes.	\N	{"root": {"type": "root", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "We use Zoom and Opalescence — two of the most respected professional protocols. In-chair sessions deliver immediate change; take-home trays deliver more durable change over two weeks. The combined approach is most patients' best option.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": "ltr", "textFormat": 0}], "direction": "ltr"}}	2	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	f	13	2026-05-20 12:55:42.719+00	2026-05-20 12:54:45.17+00
1	surgical-face	1	Face	The face,	refined.	Quiet work for the most considered part of the body.	Rhinoplasty, facelift, eyelid surgery, and the subtler refinements — performed in our ACHSI-accredited theatres with a structure-preserving, conservative approach.	\N	{"root": {"type": "root", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "We approach facial surgery as long-term investment in your face, not a single intervention. A well-judged rhinoplasty looks better at year five than year one. A deep-plane facelift outlasts a SMAS by a decade. We prefer the operation that earns its keep over time — and we will tell you when surgery is the wrong answer.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": "ltr", "textFormat": 0}], "direction": "ltr"}}	1	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	f	0	2026-05-20 12:55:41.793+00	2026-05-20 12:54:44.353+00
3	surgical-breast	1	Breast	Considered,	your own.	Conservative work, proportioned to your anatomy.	A complete repertoire of breast surgery — implant-based augmentation, lifting, reduction, and refinement — performed in our ACHSI-accredited theatres by ISAPS-member plastic surgeons. We size for proportion and longevity, not volume.	\N	{"root": {"type": "root", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "Breast surgery, in our view, is anatomical work first and aesthetic work second. We size implants in millilitres rather than cup sizes, plan incisions around lifestyle and lactation goals, and prefer the smaller intervention every time we can defend it. Recovery is supervised — daily nursing visits in a private villa, two scheduled surgeon reviews, and twelve months of telehealth follow-up after you fly home.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": "ltr", "textFormat": 0}], "direction": "ltr"}}	1	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	f	2	2026-05-20 12:55:41.933+00	2026-05-20 12:54:44.523+00
8	non-surgical-laser	3	Laser & Resurfacing	Light,	with restraint.	Gold-standard platforms, dialled to the minimum effective dose.	Fractional laser, IPL, chemical peels, and RF microneedling — used precisely, scheduled around your visit, and always with conservative settings.	\N	{"root": {"type": "root", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "Our laser suite uses Lumenis, Sciton, and Sylfirm — three of the most respected platforms in the world for fractional, IPL, and RF microneedling respectively. Settings are tailored per session, per skin type, and per season. Aggressive single-session treatments are not how we practice.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": "ltr", "textFormat": 0}], "direction": "ltr"}}	5	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	f	7	2026-05-20 12:55:42.263+00	2026-05-20 12:54:44.821+00
10	hair-fue	4	FUE Surgical	Returning,	quietly.	Single-follicle transplantation, designed to never be detected.	Sapphire FUE and DHI implantation — for hair restoration that respects what your face has always done, and that the world will never identify as transplanted.	\N	{"root": {"type": "root", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "We perform between two and four FUE cases per day, capped deliberately. Each case has one dedicated lead surgeon and a team of three certified technicians. Single follicles in the hairline, two- and three-hair units behind. Single-day or staged depending on graft count.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": "ltr", "textFormat": 0}], "direction": "ltr"}}	1	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	f	9	2026-05-20 12:55:42.432+00	2026-05-20 12:54:44.917+00
16	weight-loss-endoscopic	6	Endoscopic	Endoscopic	weight loss.	Non-incisional procedures performed through the mouth, no scars.	Intragastric balloons and endoscopic sleeve gastroplasty (ESG) — performed under sedation through the mouth, with no incisions and same-week recovery.	\N	{"root": {"type": "root", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "Endoscopic procedures are performed by our consultant gastroenterologist, with full bariatric multidisciplinary support: dietitian, behavioural health, and exercise physiology. Recovery is days, not weeks; outcomes are weeks, not minutes.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": "ltr", "textFormat": 0}], "direction": "ltr"}}	1	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	f	15	2026-05-20 12:55:42.904+00	2026-05-20 12:54:45.294+00
17	weight-loss-surgical	6	Bariatric Surgery	Bariatric	surgery.	Laparoscopic surgical pathways for serious weight loss.	Sleeve gastrectomy, gastric bypass, and revision bariatric surgery — performed laparoscopically by our consultant bariatric surgeon in our ACHSI-accredited theatres, with structured multidisciplinary support before and after.	\N	{"root": {"type": "root", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "Performed by a consultant bariatric surgeon with international fellowship training and over 1,500 cases. All procedures are laparoscopic (keyhole) with same-day mobilisation. We are conservative about combining bariatric surgery with body-contouring work — the latter is best deferred until weight has been stable for twelve months.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": "ltr", "textFormat": 0}], "direction": "ltr"}}	1	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	f	16	2026-05-20 12:55:43.069+00	2026-05-20 12:54:45.337+00
12	dental-veneers	5	Veneers	The smile,	rebuilt.	Porcelain or composite, paced to suit your visit.	Porcelain veneers, composite veneers, and complete smile makeovers — designed in collaboration with our on-staff ceramicist over three visits and fourteen days.	\N	{"root": {"type": "root", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "Our dental studio is small — two surgeries, one ceramicist on staff, conservative practice. We prefer minimal-prep veneers where the case allows, and we always include a try-in stage so you can see and feel the result before final placement.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": "ltr", "textFormat": 0}], "direction": "ltr"}}	2	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	f	11	2026-05-20 12:55:42.581+00	2026-05-20 12:54:45.057+00
15	weight-loss-medical	6	Medical	Medical weight	loss.	Pharmacological pathways, supported by nutrition and behaviour.	GLP-1 medications, structured dietitian programmes, and prescription protocols — for patients seeking sustained weight loss without surgery, with monthly monitoring and lifestyle support.	\N	{"root": {"type": "root", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "Our medical pathway is led by a consultant endocrinologist working alongside our dietitian and behavioural-health team. We prescribe TGA- and FDA-approved medications only, monitor monthly, and step down or transition to maintenance once your target is reached. We will not prescribe without ongoing supervision.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": "ltr", "textFormat": 0}], "direction": "ltr"}}	5	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	f	14	2026-05-20 12:55:42.803+00	2026-05-20 12:54:45.222+00
